The proceedings contain 12 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Particle physics, astrophysics, and cosmology school. The topics include: Basic features of high-energy Hadronic interactions; quantum Chromodynamics; selected topics from the experiments with high-energy heavy-ion collisions; flavour physics and CP violation in the standard model and beyond; the Higgs system in and beyond the standard model; Higgs searches at the LHC; messengers of the high energy universe; numerical methods and data analysis techniques in particle physics; theoretical cosmology; introduction to the ADS/CFT correspondence; welcome speech by the rector; Queimada and list of participants.